rComments: Average professor, the course is quite easy but the course page is a total mess: takes too long to find the right lectures. Additionally, the slides (if you skip lectures) are absolutely horrific to study from, often containing little to no useful information. Going to class makes this course way easier
Question how outdated the material is, but she has an experienced take on the subject. She's great.

Course itself not too difficult (although a lot of content seems to not have been updated in 10 years) - but grading for tests and paper weirdly harsh, even when it seems as though you answered the question as best as you can.
Stuckless was a very boring lecturer she often fell behind in the material. However the course was super easy and she even allowed a partial cheat sheet for the midterm test.
Very boring lecturer. Material was simple, but grades were kept low because of TA and policy..

Total train wreck of a course. Got an A in it, but grades were artificially lowered so that the class adheres to a strict bell curve. Got a horrible mark on the exam although everything was memorized word-for-word from textbook. Filed petition. TAs had to keep class average down & totally screwed over the class. Beware.
Cool material but the class itself can be very boring.  She tried to make it better with fun personal stories but they are few between
